{"title_page": "Admas University College\u2013Addis Ababa", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n|name = Admas University \n|image_name = \n|type =Higher Education\n|established = 1998 \n|city = [[Addis Ababa]]\n|country = [[Ethiopia]]\n|president = Dr Molla Tsegay\n|head_label = General Manager\n|head = Yibrah Girmay\n|website = {{URL|www.admasuniversity.edu.et}}\n}}\n'''Admas University ''' is a tertiary institution based in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]]. It was established in 1998.\n\n==Overview==\nThe Admas University is accredited by Regional Educational Bureaus, Higher Education Relevance and Quality Agency (HERQA), and the Federal Ministry of Education of Ethiopia.<ref>[http://www.au.edu.et/Accreditation.html Admas University - Accreditation]</ref> It offers both on-campus education and distance learning in various programs. These courses are in turn offered at a number of levels: certificate, diploma and degree.\n\nThe University has also started many e-Learning programs to develop the Ethiopian Higher Educational System. To reach these goals, it is currently working in partnership with internationally renowned institutions, such as [[Cisco]] and the [[University of L\u00fcbeck]] in [[Germany]].<ref>[http://www.au.edu.et/About%20Us.html Admas University - About Us] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303185920/http://www.au.edu.et/About%20Us.html |date=March 3, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nAdmas has additional branches in [[Admas University \u2013Hargeisa|Hargeisa]] and [[Admas University \u2013Garowe|Garowe]], situated in the autonomous [[Somaliland]] and [[Puntland]] regions of [[Somalia]], respectively.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.admasuniversity.edu.et Admas University homepage] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101128015341/http://oncampus.de/index.php?id=651&L=1 oncampus GmBH Cooperation Partners] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[http://www.cisco.com/web/EA/documents/pdfs/press/2007/Ethiopia_NetAcad_10_Sept_07_v2.pdf CISCO Country Transformation - Ethiopia]\n*[http://www.admasuniversity.com Admas University , Hargeisa homepage] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091130161613/http://www.higher.edu.et/index.php/herqa Higher Education Relevance and Quality Agency (HERQA)](in {{in lang|en}})\n\n{{Coord|9.0235557|38.7864765|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Admas University -Addis Ababa}}\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Ethiopia]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1998]]\n[[Category:1998 establishments in Ethiopia]]\n\n\n{{Ethiopia-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University\n|name = Admas University \n|image_name = \n|type =Higher Education\n|established = 1998 \n|city = [[Addis Ababa]]\n|country = [[Ethiopia]]\n|president = Dr Molla Tsegay\n|head_label = General Manager\n|head = Yibrah Girmay\n|website = {{URL|www.admasuniversity.edu.et}}\n}}\n'''Admas University ''' is a tertiary institution based in [[Addis Ababa]], [[Ethiopia]]. It was established in 1998.\n\n==Overview==\nThe Admas University is accredited by Regional Educational Bureaus, Higher Education Relevance and Quality Agency (HERQA), and the Federal Ministry of Education of Ethiopia.<ref>[http://www.au.edu.et/Accreditation.html Admas University - Accreditation]</ref> It offers both on-campus education and distance learning in various programs. These courses are in turn offered at a number of levels: certificate, diploma and degree.\n\nThe University has also started many e-Learning programs to develop the Ethiopian Higher Educational System. To reach these goals, it is currently working in partnership with internationally renowned institutions, such as [[Cisco]] and the [[University of L\u00fcbeck]] in [[Germany]].<ref>[http://www.au.edu.et/About%20Us.html Admas University - About Us] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303185920/http://www.au.edu.et/About%20Us.html |date=March 3, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nAdmas has additional branches in [[Admas University \u2013Hargeisa|Hargeisa]] and [[Admas University \u2013Garowe|Garowe]], situated in the autonomous [[Somaliland]] and [[Puntland]] regions of [[Somalia]], respectively.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.admasuniversity.edu.et Admas University homepage] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101128015341/http://oncampus.de/index.php?id=651&L=1 oncampus GmBH Cooperation Partners] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[http://www.cisco.com/web/EA/documents/pdfs/press/2007/Ethiopia_NetAcad_10_Sept_07_v2.pdf CISCO Country Transformation - Ethiopia]\n*[http://www.admasuniversity.com Admas University , Hargeisa homepage] (in {{in lang|en}})\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20091130161613/http://www.higher.edu.et/index.php/herqa Higher Education Relevance and Quality Agency (HERQA)](in {{in lang|en}})\n\n{{Coord|9.0235557|38.7864765|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Admas University -Addis Ababa}}\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Ethiopia]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1998]]\n[[Category:1998 establishments in Ethiopia]]\n\n{{Ethiopia-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Admas_University_College%E2%80%93Addis_Ababa"}
